item.title: C&C Generals 2 F2P
item.dc:creator: DownloadFailed
item.description:
I’ve been calling for EAs tar-and-feathering for years now. It seems like with each game they produce, they’re hammering putting another nail into their coffin. However, I will say that not all F2P games are inherently bad. TF2 did it well (generally). Tribes: Ascend is a good example. What both these games have in common is no only are they F2P, but all the content that you can compete with can be unlocked through time and effort, and most importantly, for free. But it is recommended, especially in Tribes’ case, that you spend a few bucks to help in the areas you need it most. Besides, you’re playing this kickass game that the devs have slaved over for years. They deserve a little money for their hard work.
